      "agent_text": "All recent CI runs show success. Let me check for any failed runs:\n\nThere's a recent failure on main. Let me check the details:\n\nThe failure is caused by a clipboard test crashing on CI due to missing display server. The Rust arboard library panics with `DisplayNotSet`. Let me check the latest fix PR:\n\nThere's an open PR #1170 that fixes this. Let me check it:\n\n**Summary:** CI is failing because the clipboard tests crash on Linux CI (no display server). The Rust arboard library used by `@mariozechner/clipboard` panics with `DisplayNotSet`.\n\n**Fix available:** PR #1170 by @aliou extracts the native module loading into a separate `clipboard-native.ts` file that can be properly mocked by vitest, preventing the native module from loading at all during tests.\n\nThe fix moves:\n1. Native clipboard require into `src/utils/clipboard-native.ts`\n2. Updates `clipboard-image.ts` to import from the new wrapper\n3. Changes test mock from `@mariozechner/clipboard` to the ESM wrapper `../src/utils/clipboard-native.js`\n\nThis prevents the native Rust library from loading during tests, avoiding the CI crash.",
