      "agent_text": "You're right. The simplest solution: skip the test when clipboard isn't available (CI has no display). Let me check the current test:\n\nThe issue is the Rust library **panics** (crashes the process) when there's no display. A JavaScript try/catch can't catch Rust panics.\n\nTwo clean solutions:\n\n**Option 1: Don't load the native module on Linux without a display**\n\n```typescript\n// Only load on Linux if there's a display server\nconst canLoadClipboard = process.platform !== \"linux\" || \n    Boolean(process.env.DISPLAY || process.env.WAYLAND_DISPLAY);\n\nif (canLoadClipboard) {\n    try {\n        Clipboard = require(\"@mariozechner/clipboard\");\n    } catch {\n        Clipboard = null;\n    }\n}\n```\n\n**Option 2: Skip the test in CI**\n\n```typescript\ndescribe.skipIf(process.env.CI && !process.env.DISPLAY)(\"readClipboardImage\", () => {\n```\n\nOption 1 is better since it also fixes the actual runtime behavior (don't crash if someone runs pi on a headless Linux server). The clipboard module is useless without a display anyway.\n\nWhich approach do you prefer?",
